(General reach notes): 0.17 mi up from SCC4 division. Park in small meadow turnout on right surrounded by wooden fence. End at pool ~8 m below large tire on right bank and just above 2 large aspen logs across stream. Lots of big "mosquito moths." Lots of moss on rocks. Large ants on the wood. Lots of fallen aspen logs. Lots of nettles! Lots of unstable islands. Lots of boulder and wood on banks make it difficult to determine bankfull. Seems entrenced based on FPW.
